---
import BaseHead from '../../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
import Header from '../../components/Header.astro';
import { SITE_DESCRIPTION, SITE_TITLE } from '../../consts';

const pageTitle = 'DeepL vs Google Translate: AI Translation Accuracy Test in 2026? - ' + SITE_TITLE;
const pageDescription = 'We tested DeepL and Google Translate side by side to find the best free AI translation tool for 2026.';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title={pageTitle} description={pageDescription} />
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<main>
			<h1>DeepL vs Google Translate: AI Translation Accuracy Test in 2026</h1>
			<p>In 2026, AI translation tools are essential for anyone working across languages. We tested the two most popular options side by side.</p>

			<h2>Quick Comparison</h2>
			<table>
				<tr><th>Feature</th><th>DeepL</th><th>Google Translate</th></tr>
				<tr><td>Price</td><td>Free tier limited, Pro from $8.74/mo</td><td>Completely free</td></tr>
				<tr><td>Languages</td><td>31 languages</td><td>133 languages</td></tr>
				<tr><td>Accuracy</td><td>More natural, context-aware</td><td>Good for common phrases</td></tr>
				<tr><td>Document Translation</td><td>Yes (PDF, Word, PPT)</td><td>Yes (limited)</td></tr>
				<tr><td>Privacy</td><td>Deletes text after translation</td><td>May use data for improvement</td></tr>
			</table>

			<h2>DeepL Review</h2>
			<p>DeepL has become the gold standard for AI translation quality, especially for European languages.</p>
			<h3>Pros</h3>
			<ul>
				<li>Most natural-sounding translations</li>
				<li>Excellent for European languages</li>
				<li>Document translation built-in</li>
			</ul>
			<h3>Cons</h3>
			<ul>
				<li>Only 31 languages supported</li>
				<li>Free version has character limits</li>
			</ul>
			<p><strong>Best for:</strong> Professionals, translators, and anyone needing high-quality European language translation.</p>
			<p><a href="[AFFILIATE_LINK_DEEPL]">Try DeepL Free</a></p>

			<h2>Google Translate Review</h2>
			<p>Google Translate is the most widely used translation tool, supporting over 130 languages.</p>
			<h3>Pros</h3>
			<ul>
				<li>Completely free</li>
				<li>133 languages supported</li>
				<li>Real-time camera translation</li>
			</ul>
			<h3>Cons</h3>
			<ul>
				<li>Less natural for complex sentences</li>
				<li>Privacy concerns for sensitive text</li>
			</ul>
			<p><strong>Best for:</strong> Travelers, casual users, and anyone needing quick translations in rare languages.</p>
			<p><a href="[AFFILIATE_LINK_GOOGLE]">Use Google Translate</a></p>

			<h2>Editor's Picks</h2>
			<ul>
				<li><strong>Best for Accuracy:</strong> DeepL</li>
				<li><strong>Best for Coverage:</strong> Google Translate</li>
				<li><strong>Best Free Option:</strong> Google Translate</li>
			</ul>

			<h2>FAQ</h2>
			<p><strong>Q: Is DeepL really better than Google Translate?</strong><br>A: For European languages and natural-sounding text, yes. For rare languages, Google Translate wins.</p>
			<p><strong>Q: Can I translate documents for free?</strong><br>A: Google Translate offers free document translation with limits. DeepL's free tier also allows documents but with size restrictions.</p>
			<p><strong>Q: Which is better for business use?</strong><br>A: DeepL Pro is better for business due to higher privacy standards and more natural translations.</p>

			<p><em>Disclaimer: This post contains affiliate links. We may earn a commission if you purchase through these links.</em></p>
		</main>
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>